description:
Responsible for full round office administration duties but not limited to office renovation, facilities management, vendor management, central procurement, lease management, and general office administration
Manage various vendor contracts and leasing agreements for all branches & offices in Hong Kong;
Manage the central procurement and tendering agreement for Company expenses, incl, office renovation, IT equipment and systems
Coordinates with external supplier / vendor of different office systems (e.g. telephone system, photocopier, office furniture, office equipment; security system);
Assist senior management in formulating, implementing and reviewing administration policies, procedures and guidelines;
Assist in budget preparation and control to ensure smooth operations in a cost-effective manner;
Development needs and to ensure compliance of Environmental , Health & Safety regulations;
Work closely with internal & external parties on coordination of business assignments;
Handle ad hoc projects as assigned by management;
Consults with insurance consultant to arrange suitable insurance policies for head office and branches in Hong Kong. Handles and follows up claim cases.
Review China projects related to office renovation and operation of Admin Department in China office

Job Requirements:

Higher Diploma/ Associate Degree holder in Facilities Management / Property Management / Business Administration or equivalent
Atleast 10 year experience in office admin / facilities management services.
People Management experienced is a must
Candidate with Financial Institution, MNC is preferred
Ability to deal with different levels of external business partners / contractors
Ability to work independently and able to work under pressure
Have knowledge of central procurement will be an advantage
Good command of spoken English, Cantonese and Putonghua a plus

Reporting to the Senior Property Manager, the incumbent will assume overall responsibility for the management and operation of a diverse portfolio of the Group including office buildings, shopping malls, commercial buildings and serviced apartments in Hong Kong.  He/She will oversee the day-to-day Estate Management and Technical Services, to provide a full range of services in the highest standard.

Requirements:

Degree or above in Surveying, Facilities Management, Property/Housing Management or related disciplines;
6 years of property management experience for established developers, 3 years of which at supervisory level;
Less experience candidates will be considered for Senior Property Officer role;
Hands on experience in managing grade A commercial properties are essential;
Good communication, presentation and interpersonal skills;
Self-motivated and attentive to details are required.

We offer attractive remuneration package to the right candidate.  Interested parties please send full resume including current and expected salaries to the Head of Human Resources & Administration, Man Hing Hong Group, 31/F Man Yee Building, 68 Des Voeux Road Central, Hong Kong (website: www.mhh.com.hk)

(All personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only)

Key Responsibilities

Provide general office administration and clerical supports;
Assist in the service and internal operation audit for HK and Macau property portfolio;
Provide support and participate in the electronic procurement system;
Assist in ISO Quality Management System;
Assist ad-hoc duties as assigned.

Requirements

Degree in Business Administration, Journalism or related disciplines are preferred;
1-2 years' relevant experience in commercial or public sectors;
Good command of both spoken and written English and Chinese;
Proficiency in computer knowledge.

We offer long-term career prospect and competitive remuneration package to the appointed candidate. Please apply in confidence with your detailed resume stating your current and expected salary to Group Human Resources Department

by email to recruit(at)shuntakgroup.com

or mail to Penthouse 39/F, West Tower, Shun Tak Centre, 200 Connaught Road Central, Hong Kong

(Please quote reference number and applied position)

The information supplied by the applicants will be used for recruitment purpose and in accordance with the Personal Data (Privacy) Policy of Shun Tak Group (a copy of which will be provided upon request). Personal data of the unsuccessful applicants will be destroyed in twelve months from the date of application. Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.

www.shuntakgroup.com

Duties
The appointee will be required but not limited to:
lead a service team to handle a full range of duties related to facilities management, such as cleaning, security, catering, landscaping, etc.;
develop and implement office administrative systems and procedures;
develop and monitor annual operating expense budgets;
handle facilities services and administrative services requests;
monitor the performance of vendors, suppliers, facilities management service providers;
prepare services contracts, proposals, reports, policies and procedures;
supervise and manage in-house and outsourced teams to provide administrative and facilities management support;
provide support services on space planning and minor maintenance and improvement projects; and
work on irregular hours including Saturdays, Sundays and Public Holidays if needed.
Requirements
Applicants should:
possess a recognized Bachelor’s degree with at least 5 years of relevant experience preferably in Facilities Management / Housing Management / Surveying or related disciplines;
have the ability to perform multi-tasks;
be able to work independently and have good leadership and coordination skills;
be self-motivated with positive work attitude and have good team spirit;
possess good planning, problem-solving, interpersonal and organization skills;
have excellent computer literacy in MS applications including Chinese word processing;
have good command of both written and spoken in English and Chinese; and
preferably be a member of HKIS / RICS / HKIH / Registered Professional Housing Manager or other related professional qualification is preferred.
Salary will be competitive and commensurate with qualifications and experience.
To apply, please submit your application letter, resume and a completed application form (available at http://www.twc.edu.hk/en/Administration_Units/hro/career/application_guideline) by mail to the Human Resources Office, Tung Wah College Cheung Kung Hai Memorial Building, 90A Shantung Street, Mongkok, Kowloon.  Please quote the reference number of the post in the application letter and on the envelope.  The College reserves the right to fill or not to fill the post.  Applicants who are not contacted by the College 4 months after the application deadline may consider their applications unsuccessful.
Application Deadline: 27 January 2022 (Thursday)
All information and personal data collected will be used solely for recruitment related purposes. For more information about the College, please visit our website: http://www.twc.edu.hk.
WE ARE AN EQUAL OPPORTUNITIES EMPLOYER

Responsibilities

Manage and oversee the operations of property management services;
Supervise a team to provide quality property management services to clients;
Ensure compliance with relevant ordinance and regulations;
Liaise with clients, supplier and internal parties;
Handle ad hoc assignments as required

Requirements

Degree holder or above in property management or related disciplines;
Member of CIH / HKIH is preferred or other recognized professional bodies;
Holder of provisional PMP License (Tier 1) is preferred;
5 years or above relevant experience in property management of which 2 years should be at managerial level;
Strong leadership, communication, and interpersonal skills;
Proficient in both written and spoken English and Chinese

Candidates with less experience will be considered for the post of Senior Property Officer.

Our Properties Department is responsible for :

Rental of our two commercial buildings;
Direct management of our own buildings, with our sister “Building Services” department maintaining all essential building services.

The successful candidate will assist the department head to fulfill the department’s responsibility, with the help of two building officers.

This position entails the regular performance of (but NOT limited to) the following :

Liaise with agents for potential tenants;
Negotiate with potential tenants for new rentals and existing tenants for renewals;
Supervise our own building-management staff;
Closely monitor new tenants’ fitting-out process to ensure strict adherence to renovation restrictions.

This position will have the prospect of promotion to Assistant Manager on proven performance of his/her duties.

Minimum requirements:

Holder of an associate degree or equivalent.  Holder of the Hong Kong Institute of Real Estate Administrators accreditation will have an advantage;
3 years’ relevant experience in rental of commercial space & building management;
Proficiency in both English & Chinese (Cantonese and Putonghua);
Good computer skills for MS office, especially with Excel, and Chinese input.

We are looking for an individual who has substantial hands-on experience, pays meticulous attention to details and accuracy, is not afraid to ask questions, is proactive by temperament and is able to see beyond his/her own department and understand the priorities of the company as a whole.  In addition, if your past or current work can show that you have good communication, interpersonal & supervisory skills, you will have an advantage.

Interested parties should email full resume, including HKCEE/DSE and HKAL results or equivalent, current and expected annual salary and availability by clicking "Apply Now".

All personal data will be treated in strict confidence and used for this recruitment only.

Job Description

• Manage the on-site team and develop protocol, practice align with policies to perform the security & service

• Partner with business units to identify security deficiencies, and develop customized policies and procedures to gain compliance with regulations

• Provide advice and counsel on complex physical security, internal fraud investigations, prevention, life safety risk, fire safety, crisis management, and emergency response issues

• Handle and manage securing classified and sensitive information from the work environment and assigned task

• Prepare and present collected data, information, report and documentation for the scope related, including invoice and accruals

• To conduct threat assessment to the business, event activity and site

• Maintains a positive, professional environment in full compliance with applicable laws, regulations, policies and procedures; ensures that security force understand and comply with applicable laws, regulations, policies and procedure

Requirement

• Degree holder in any discipline;

• A minimum 3 years of experience in a supervisory position in the corporate security industry;

• Strong sense of security awareness, tough and with good communication and interpersonal skill

• Good knowledge in health, safety and environment;

• Proficient in both written and spoken English and Chinese;

• Strong prioritizing abilities, analytical and problem-solving skills;

• Must be competent and literate with computers;

• Immediate available is a definite advantage

Job Highlights 

Responsible for managing properties as assigned 
3-6 years' relevant experience 
HK$20,000-$25,000 per month 

Job Description 
Responsibilities: 


Responsible for managing properties as assigned; 
Liaise with owners and tenants/ contractors; 
Supervise and monitor the contractors and technicians about the repair work and renovation projects 
Requirements: 

Degree or Diploma holder, preferably in property management; 
Holding an Estate Agent's Licence or a Salesperson's Licence (Preferable); 
Proficient in BMO, DMC and/ or related ordinances; 
Good knowledge on property market; 
Can anticipate potential issue and make precaution; 
Minimum 3-6 years' relevant working experience; 
Good interpersonal skill, proactive, innovative and problem solving ability; 
Good command of both written and spoken English and Chinese. 

Working Location: Causeway Bay 
Working Hours: Monday- Friday 10AM- 6PM ; Saturday 10AM-1PM 
Benefits: Bank Holidays, Lunch Meal

Responsibilities

Manage and oversee daily operations of deluxe properties;
Being the 2nd in-charge of the management team to provide quality service to clients;
Ensure compliance with DMC and relevant ordinances;
Attend meetings with Management Committee members of The Incorporated Owners to maintain good relationship;
Liaise with clients, suppliers and contractors;
Handle ad hoc assignments, as required.

Requirements

Degree holder or above in property management or related disciplines;
Member of CIH / HKIH or other recognized professional bodies;
Possession of Property Management Practitioner (Tier 1) License being an advantage;
At least 7 years' solid experience in luxurious residential property management;
Strong leadership with good communication and interpersonal skills;
Enthusiastic to work and self-motivating;
Fluent in oral English & Cantonese;
Proficient in written English & Chinese;
Immediate availability is highly preferred.

Interested parties please send resume with expected salary by e-mail to: Apply Now
(All personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.)
